Result:

` javascript
const list = names = {
  return names.reduce( (prev, current, index, array) = {
    if (index === 0){
      return current.name;
    }
    else if (index === array.length - 1){
      return ${prev} & ${current.name};
    } 
    else {
      return ${prev}, ${current.name};
    }
  }, '');
 }
